properties.areaDesc: Upper Tanana Valley and the Fortymile Country
properties.headline: Wind Chill Warning issued January 11 at 3:16PM AKST until January 13 at 12:00PM AKST by NWS Fairbanks AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...Dangerously cold wind chills to 60 below expected. The
dangerously cold wind chills will cause frostbite in as little
as 10 minutes to exposed skin.

* WHERE...along the Yukon River near Eagle.

* WHEN...Midnight tonight until noon Monday.
properties.instruction:
A Wind Chill Warning means the combination of very cold air and
sustained wind speeds of 15 mph or more will create dangerously
low wind chill values. Frost bite can occur quickly and even
hypothermia or death if precautions are not taken.

NWSheadline: WIND CHILL WARNING IN EFFECT FROM MIDNIGHT TONIGHT TO NOON AKST MONDAY
